sing on the active class. It doesn’t create parsers, so I might assert that `reflectedVersion.toFullString()` contains \\\"jackson-core,\\\" though that hardcodes internal details, which isn’t ideal. It could be better to use JsonFactory for this comparison. There’s a potential issue if `VersionUtil.versionFor(JsonReadFeature.class)` dynamically loads PackageVersion first, followed by `new JsonFactory().version()` for static loading. I want to ensure no compile issues arise, and it seems okay if there are no differences for new files in the final version.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused `VersionUtil` coverage for `software.amazon.awssdk:third-party-jackson-core:2.34.0`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added `VersionUtilTest.java` with tests that exercise:\n  - `VersionUtil.versionFor(...)`, reaching:\n    - `Class.forName(...)`\n    - `Class.getDeclaredConstructor(...)`\n    - `Constructor.newInstance(...)`\n  - `VersionUtil.mavenVersionFor(...)`, reaching:\n    - `ClassLoader.getResourceAsStream(...)`\n- Added a test `pom.properties` resource under `src/test/resources/META-INF/maven/...`.\n- Removed the scaffold placeholder test file.\n\nI did not run tests, per workflow instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_059960f421d74b2d0169f912dcb1a481a0afdba51d9c9d549e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 876, "output": 657, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34813, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777930961228, "responseId": "resp_059960f421d74b2d0169f912d207fc81a0a7b73315b2e79cdd"}, "toolResults": []}
